  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Level Frameworks:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) obligations\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Enhanced scrutiny for high-risk sectors\n- International information sharing\n\n4. Penalties for Non-Compliance:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Loss of business licenses\n- Personal liability for executives\n\n5. Sectors Covered:\n- Banking\n- Financial institutions\n- Real estate\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive regulatory mechanisms and international cooperation.",
